      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "AUTUMN GLOW (7) wonder mare who puts her unbeaten record on the line as she steps out to this trip for the first time. Goes to a new pain barrier here after she made a mess of inferior opposition with a slashing win in the G1 George Ryder Stakes over 1500m at Rosehill. Maps well and should prove too sharp again. DUBAI HONOUR (1) tough old war horse with a glowing record in this race. Almost pinched the race when nailed late by AELIANA over 2400m in the G1 Tancred first-up. Sure to come on for this, and William Haggas will be looking for the blinkers to do the trick. SIR DELIUS (2) snagged back in the small field and closed strongly to finish third in the G1 Ranvet over 2000m at Rosehill. Should be spot on now and expect to see Williams have him closer today. LINDERMANN (4) rough place chance.",
